"title": "7972: tongues, gift of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7972: tongues, gift of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The divine enabling of a believer to use a language, unknown to the speaker. The gift of tongues may be used to praise God or to utter a message from God that, supplemented by the gift of interpretation of tongues, edifies other believers. Note that “tongues” can simply mean “other languages” at times.</p>\n<h2>Tongues is a gift of the Holy Spirit</h2>\n<h3>It is given to individual believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:4\">ACT 2:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:11\">1CO 12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:30\">1CO 12:30</a> <em>it is not universal among Christians</em></p>\n<h3>It was foretold in the OT</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:21\">1CO 14:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:11\">ISA 28:11</a></p>\n<h3>It is a divine gift in response to faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:17\">MRK 16:17</a></strong></p>\n<h3>It may be given through the laying on of hands</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:6\">ACT 19:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>It is a sign of the presence of the Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:44-Acts10:46\">ACT 10:44–10:46</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Tongues in relation to other gifts</h2>\n<h3>The need for love</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:1\">1CO 13:1</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The need for prophecy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:4-1Cor14:6\">1CO 14:4–14:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The need for intelligibility</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:9\">1CO 14:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:13\">1CO 14:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:16-1Cor14:19\">1CO 14:16–14:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:23\">1CO 14:23</a></p>\n<h3>The need for interpretation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:8-1Cor12:10\">1CO 12:8–12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:12-1Cor14:13\">1CO 14:12–14:13</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The transience of tongues</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:8\">1CO 13:8</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The use of tongues within the church</h2>\n<h3>In prayer and praise</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:26\">ROM 8:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:14-1Cor14:15\">1CO 14:14–14:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:26\">1CO 14:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:28\">1CO 14:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:18\">EPH 6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:20\">JUD 1:20</a></p>\n<h3>For the benefit of believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:7-1Cor12:10\">1CO 12:7–12:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:5\">1CO 14:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:16-1Cor14:17\">1CO 14:16–14:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:26\">1CO 14:26</a></p>\n<h3>In public it needs to be augmented by the gift of interpretation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:26-1Cor14:28\">1CO 14:26–14:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:30\">1CO 12:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:5\">1CO 14:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:13\">1CO 14:13</a></p>",
